\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true,\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$2d\\\"}}]\\n2e:T47b,{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"FAQPage\\\",\\\"mainEntity\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Where can I take my dog in Chapel Hill?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Southern Community Park and Homestead Park both feature fenced dog parks. For walks, the Bolin Creek Trail and the UNC campus (leashed) are fantastic options.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Is Franklin Street dog-friendly?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Yes, many outdoor patios along Franklin Street welcome dogs. It’s a vibrant area for a walk, especially when the university is in session, but it can get crowded.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are there leash laws in Chapel Hill?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Chapel Hill and Orange County strictly enforce leash laws. Dogs must be under control at all times, which usually means on a leash unless in a designated area.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Can dogs hike at Occoneechee Mountain?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Nearby in Hillsborough, Occoneechee Mountain State Natural Area welcomes leashed dogs on its trails, offering some of the best views in the region.\\\"}}]}26:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true,\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$2e\\\"}}]\\n27:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true,\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"itemListElement\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\